# Recall Touch — Product Doctrine v2

You are building **Recall Touch**, an **AI phone communication platform** that handles inbound/outbound calls, captures leads, books appointments, and follows up — so businesses never miss revenue.

Built on: Next.js 14+ App Router, TypeScript, Supabase, Vapi (voice AI), ElevenLabs (TTS), Claude (intelligence), Stripe, Vercel.

## What this product does

- AI voice agents that answer calls 24/7, qualify callers, book appointments, and follow up
- Unified inbox for calls, SMS, email, and WhatsApp in one place
- Lead capture, pipeline management, and scoring tied to phone conversations
- Outbound campaigns (call + SMS sequences) for follow-up and re-engagement
- Analytics showing call outcomes, conversion rates, peak hours, and revenue impact
- Call intelligence for transcript analysis, coaching scores, and trend detection
- Integrations with CRM, calendar, and automation tools via webhooks and OAuth

## What to build when asked

You are authorized to implement **any feature** in the categories above. This includes but is not limited to:

- Dashboards with KPIs, stat cards, sparklines, trend arrows, charts
- Analytics with area charts, donut charts, heatmaps, funnels, AI insights
- Lead pipeline with Kanban board (drag-and-drop), lead detail pages, scoring, tags, notes
- Campaign builder with audience selection, sequence timeline, scheduling, compliance
- Call detail views with audio player, waveform, transcript, AI summary, actions taken
- Inbox with threaded conversations, real-time messages, quick reply, contact panel
- Agent builder with industry templates, knowledge import, behavior rules, test calls
- Settings with integrations (OAuth for Google Calendar, CRM webhooks, Slack), billing, team management
- Command palette (⌘K), keyboard shortcuts, notifications, mobile responsive layouts
- Any UI component: buttons, modals, sheets, badges, tooltips, tables, timelines, charts

## Design standard

- **Premium quality**: Linear/Vercel/Raycast-grade polish
- **Dark theme only**: bg #0A0A0B, surface #111113, elevated #1A1A1D
- **Animations**: Framer Motion with `ease: 'easeOut'` (string, not array)
- **Loading**: Skeleton screens matching actual layout, not spinners
- **Components**: Custom only — no shadcn, Chakra, or MUI
- **Icons**: Lucide React
- **Fonts**: Inter (body), JetBrains Mono (code/data)
- **Copy**: Authoritative, concise. No "just", "simply", "easily", "leverage"

## Architecture rules

- TypeScript strict mode
- Server Components by default, `'use client'` only when needed
- All Supabase queries through typed client in `src/lib/supabase/`
- Error boundaries on every route segment
- `cn()` utility (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional classes
- Co-locate page-specific components with their page files
